y loss, with only two brothers remaining from immediate family. Has a strained relationship with one brother due to a dispute over inheritance.", "created_at": "2025-07-22T12:20:04.871733+00:00"}, {"note": "Lives in Spain with wife, two children, and mother-in-law.", "created_at": "2025-07-22T12:20:05.046313+00:00"}, {"note": "Experiencing a lack of motivation and feeling stuck in a rut, seeking to improve follow-through on personal goals.", "created_at": "2025-07-22T12:25:37.793736+00:00"}, {"note": "Father of two children", "created_at": "2025-07-22T13:02:18.083801+00:00"}, {"note": "Carpenter with a strong interest in woodworking", "created_at": "2025-07-22T13:02:18.266214+00:00"}], "coach_state": {"who_you_are": ["Dad", "Carpenter", "Engineer", "Hard Worker"], "current_phase": "identity_brainstorming", "identity_focus": "maker_of_money", "who_you_want_to_be": ["Business Owner", "Good Public Speaker"]}, "chat_messages": [{"role": "coach", "content": "Hi! It's nice to meet you! My name is Leigh Ann.", "timestamp": "2025-07-22T11:45:12.348680+00:00"}, {"role": "user", "content": "Hi!", "timestamp": "2025-07-22T11:45:32.331560+00:00"}, {"role": "coach", "content": "To get us started, I'd like to explain a little bit about what we're going to do together here so you've got an idea of how all this is going to work. Are you ok with that?", "timestamp": "2025-07-22T11:45:36.137972+00:00"}, {"role": "user", "content": "That sounds great", "timestamp": "2025-07-22T11:45:46.815216+00:00"}, {"role": "coach", "content": "Perfect! So here's the thing - most people try to change their lives through brute force and willpower. Like telling themselves 'I need to work out more' or 'I should save money.' But willpower always runs out, right?\\n\\nWhat we're going to do differently is start with Identity. So instead of forcing yourself to go to the gym, you become a Warrior who naturally trains. Instead of stressing about money, you become a Wealth Architect who builds abundance.\\n\\nCan you see the distinction between those two approaches?", "timestamp": "2025-07-22T11:45:50.030845+00:00"}, {"role": "user", "content": "I can", "timestamp": "2025-07-22T11:46:29.806035+00:00"}, {"role": "coach", "content": "Great! So instead of organizing your life into external buckets like Career, Health, Finance, we flip it inward. We ask 'Who are you in relationship to your health?' Maybe you're a Warrior, or an Athlete, or a Vitality Seeker.\\n\\nDoes that make sense to you?", "timestamp": "2025-07-22T11:46:32.872393+00:00"}, {"role": "user", "content": "It does", "timestamp": "2025-07-22T11:46:44.350404+00:00"}, {"role": "coach", "content": "Here's the cool part - you're not just one thing. You might be a Warrior with your health, a Wealth Architect with money, and a Loving Partner in relationships. We're going to create a bunch of different Identities that represent these different parts of you. Pretty wild concept, right?", "timestamp": "2025-07-22T11:46:47.178701+00:00"}, {"role": "user", "content": "Yeah", "timestamp": "2025-07-22T11:47:16.924729+00:00"}, {"role": "coach", "content": "And here's how it works day-to-day. Instead of forcing yourself through tasks, you just ask 'Who needs to handle this?' Then you step into that identity. So if you need to tackle your budget, you don't struggle with it - you let your Wealth Architect handle it. Makes sense when you think about it that way.\\n\\nWhat do you think about applying this approach to your daily life?", "timestamp": "2025-07-22T11:47:20.116672+00:00"}, {"role": "user", "content": "I think I'm going to like this", "timestamp": "2025-07-22T11:47:51.652781+00:00"}, {"role": "coach", "content": "Wonderful! I'm excited to dive deeper with you. Before we get into the actual Identity work, I'd love to get to know you better. The more I understand about you and your world, the better I can help. So let's chat - I'll ask you some questions, and you can share as much or as little as feels right. Sound good?", "timestamp": "2025-07-22T11:47:54.716299+00:00"}, {"role": "user", "content": "That sounds great", "timestamp": "2025-07-22T11:52:21.642976+00:00"}, {"role": "coach", "content": "Fantastic! Let's start with something simple. Where did you grow up?", "timestamp": "2025-07-22T11:52:24.079338+00:00"}, {"role": "user", "content": "My early childhood was in Norcross, GA, a suburb on the north side of Atlanta. When I was 15, we moved to Homer, GA which was about an hour north of my Norcross home in the country", "timestamp": "2025-07-22T11:54:27.666873+00:00"}, {"role": "coach", "content": "That sounds like quite a shift from suburbia to the countryside! How did that move impact you? Did you find it challenging or did you enjoy the change?", "timestamp": "2025-07-22T11:54:31.228509+00:00"}, {"role": "user", "content": "It was a love hate thing really. We moved up there to be closer to my grandparents on my moms side, who I was very close with. My Grandmother loved the country and animals and farming and all that. They owned 165 acres in Homer since before I was born and they moved there in the late 1990's. So I was happy to be with them but I didn't fit in very much with the country crowd. I felt like an outsider.", "timestamp": "2025-07-22T11:57:46.473203+00:00"}, {"role": "coach", "content": "It sounds like you had a deep connection with your grandparents, especially your grandmother, which must have been comforting during the move. Being close to family can be such a blessing, even if the environment feels a bit foreign. Itâ€™s understandable to feel like an outsider when transitioning to a new setting, especially one so different from what you were used to. How did you navigate those feelings of being an outsider? Did you find any ways to connect with the new community or did you find solace in other areas?", "timestamp": "2025-07-22T11:57:50.846605+00:00"}, {"role": "user", "content": "No I dug my heels in on being different. I didn't want to have anything to do with the regular crowd so I found the outsiders group. In hindsight, I would have been better off not hanging out with them. I eventually did find a better group of friends that I stayed with for a few years.", "timestamp": "2025-07-22T12:01:16.316565+00:00"}, {"role": "coach", "content": "It's interesting how sometimes our initial choices, even if they don't seem ideal in hindsight, can lead us to valuable lessons and eventually to the right people. It sounds like you found your way to a group that resonated more with who you were becoming. \\n\\nLet's shift gears a bitâ€”I'd love to hear about what you're doing these days. What do you do for a living, and how did you find your way into that field?", "timestamp": "2025-07-22T12:01:21.458348+00:00"}, {"role": "user", "content": "I guess you could say I'm a software engineer though I have no formal training. I used to be a control room operator at a nuclear power plant. My wife is from Spain and about 4 years ago we decided to move to Malaga. That required a career change so I taught myself how to be a full stack developer", "timestamp": "2025-07-22T12:03:47.866431+00:00"}, {"role": "coach", "content": "Wow, that's quite a journey! Transitioning from a control room operator at a nuclear power plant to a self-taught full stack developer is impressive. It takes a lot of dedication and adaptability to make such a significant career shift, especially when moving to a new country like Spain. How has this change impacted your life and your sense of identity? Do you find that your work as a developer aligns with who you are or who you want to become?", "timestamp": "2025-07-22T12:03:52.668075+00:00"}, {"role": "user", "content": "Yes - though I really do miss my old job. But this one is interesting enough and challenging enough to keep me occupied and sufficiently stimulated. There are a lot of benefits as well. I can work from home and I get to make my own hours.", "timestamp": "2025-07-22T12:05:42.304539+00:00"}, {"role": "coach", "content": "It sounds like you've found a balance that works well for you, even if there are aspects of your old job that you miss. The flexibility and autonomy of working from home can be incredibly rewarding, especially when it aligns with your lifestyle and personal goals. \\n\\nSince we've touched on your career and the transition you've made, I'd love to hear a bit about your life outside of work. What are some things you love to do in your free time? Any hobbies or interests that are a big part of your life?", "timestamp": "2025-07-22T12:05:47.733145+00:00"}, {"role": "user", "content": "I really like to travel. I did that a lot with my wife a while back - before we had kids. Now that they are old enough, we're starting to travel again and I'm really happy about that. I like a wide variety of other things. I played the piano for a long time (haven't played seriously in many years though), I really enjoy woodworking and I had a full blown wood shop in my garage when I lived in the states.", "timestamp": "2025-07-22T12:08:50.353401+00:00"}, {"role": "coach", "content": "It sounds like you have a rich tapestry of interests! Traveling with your family must be such a wonderful way to create new memories together. It's great that you're able to share those experiences with your kids now that they're old enough.\\n\\nYour passion for woodworking and music adds such a creative dimension to your life. Having had a full-blown wood shop must have been a fantastic outlet for your creativity and craftsmanship. Do you find that these hobbies influence how you approach your work or other areas of your life?\\n\\nBefore we move on, I'd love to hear a little about your family if you're comfortable sharing. Who's in your world these days?", "timestamp": "2025-07-22T12:08:54.652736+00:00"}, {"role": "user", "content": "Honestly, not many are left. My Father died 20 years ago from lung cancer. My Grandmother (the one who likes farming and animals) died 3 years after that. Both my fathers parents passed away. My mothers dad died as well. And then my mother died last year. All that is left from my immediate family is 2 brothers. One of them I don't talk to because we got in a huge fight over my mothers inheritance. \\nI have my wife and two children who live with me here in Spain. My wife only has her mother as immediate family - she lives with us too.", "timestamp": "2025-07-22T12:19:56.807148+00:00"}, {"role": "coach", "content": "Thank you for sharing that with me. It sounds like you've experienced a lot of loss, and I can imagine how challenging that must have been. It's wonderful that you have your wife, children, and mother-in-law with you in Spain, creating a new chapter together. Family dynamics can be complex, especially when it comes to things like inheritance, and it's understandable that these situations can create distance.\\n\\nWith your family and interests in mind, I'm curious about what you're hoping to get out of this coaching journey. Is there a particular area of your life you're looking to explore or transform?", "timestamp": "2025-07-22T12:20:01.792712+00:00"}, {"role": "user", "content": "I just feel like I'm in a rut. I'm finding it hard to follow through on any of what I want to do. I know what I should be doing but I just don't have the motivation to actually do anything when the rubber hits the road. Id like to try and fix that if I can.", "timestamp": "2025-07-22T12:25:30.585105+00:00"}, {"role": "coach", "content": "Thank you for being so open about where you're at. Feeling stuck can be really frustrating, especially when you know what you want to achieve but can't seem to muster the motivation to get there. This is a great starting point for our work together.\\n\\nWe're going to explore the different identities you inhabit in your life right nowâ€”these could be roles, qualities, or ways you see yourself, big or small. By understanding who you are today, we can start to uncover the natural motivations and energies that might be lying dormant.\\n\\nOnce we've explored who you are today, we'll also look at who you might want to become in the future. How does that sound?", "timestamp": "2025-07-22T12:25:37.439329+00:00"}, {"role": "user", "content": "Sounds good to me", "timestamp": "2025-07-22T12:27:24.000363+00:00"}, {"role": "coach", "content": "Great! Let's dive into it. To start, think about the different roles and identities you currently embody in your life. These could be related to your work, family, hobbies, or any other aspect of your life. For example, you might identify as a software engineer, a father, a husband, or even a woodworking enthusiast.\\n\\nTake a moment and share with me who you are right now.", "timestamp": "2025-07-22T12:27:28.992515+00:00"}, {"role": "user", "content": "Dad is a good one since I have 2 kids. \\nCarpenter is a good one. Engineer I like", "timestamp": "2025-07-22T13:02:12.781778+00:00"}, {"role": "coach", "content": "I love those! Being a dad is such a profound identity, especially with two kids keeping you on your toes. And it's wonderful to see your passion for carpentry and engineering shining throughâ€”those are such creative and analytical roles, respectively.\\n\\nWhat else comes to mind? Are there any other roles or qualities that you feel are part of who you are right now?", "timestamp": "2025-07-22T13:02:19.764300+00:00"}, {"role": "user", "content": "I work hard.", "timestamp": "2025-07-22T13:04:45.995739+00:00"}, {"role": "coach", "content": "That's a fantastic quality to acknowledgeâ€”being a hard worker is such a valuable part of who you are, especially when balancing roles as a dad, carpenter, and engineer. It speaks to your dedication and perseverance.\\n\\nLet's capture these identities: Dad, Carpenter, Engineer, and Hard Worker.\\n\\nNow, let's stretch this a little. Who do you aspire to be? Think about any dreams or roles you haven't stepped into yet but feel drawn to. It could be something related to your passions, like woodworking, or even a completely new venture. What comes to mind?", "timestamp": "2025-07-22T13:04:51.619371+00:00"}, {"role": "user", "content": "I want to be a business owner", "timestamp": "2025-07-22T13:06:27.713029+00:00"}, {"role": "coach", "content": "That's an exciting aspiration! Becoming a business owner can open up so many possibilities for creativity and independence. It aligns beautifully with your skills in engineering and carpentry, perhaps even allowing you to blend those talents into a unique venture.\\n\\nLet's add \\"Business Owner\\" to your aspirational identities. Is there anything else that comes to mind when you think about who you want to become? Maybe something related to your love for woodworking or another passion?", "timestamp": "2025-07-22T13:06:33.941525+00:00"}, {"role": "user", "content": "I want to be a good public speaker.", "timestamp": "2025-07-22T13:07:03.303581+00:00"}, {"role": "coach", "content": "That's a wonderful aspiration! Being a good public speaker can enhance your ability to share your ideas and passions, whether it's about your work, your experiences, or even your journey as a business owner. It can also be a powerful tool for personal growth and connecting with others.\\n\\nLet's add \\"Good Public Speaker\\" to your list of aspirational identities. Here's what we have so far:\\n\\n- **Who You Are**: Dad, Carpenter, Engineer, Hard Worker\\n- **Who You Want To Be**: Business Owner, Good Public Speaker\\n\\nIs there anything else you'd like to add, or do you feel ready to move on to the next step?", "timestamp": "2025-07-22T13:07:08.847861+00:00"}, {"role": "user", "content": "I think we could move on for now", "timestamp": "2025-07-22T13:10:50.080060+00:00"}, {"role": "coach", "content": "Great! Now, let's make sure we're covering all the critical areas of your life. Let us create a balanced, powerful, and intentional version of you so you are fully expressed across every area of your life. This n