ons and Talents?"}], "identities": [{"name": "Humble Perspective", "notes": ["Captures Casey's grounded, grateful, and humble approach to meaning and perspectiveâ€”recognizing his smallness in the grand scheme and appreciating the luck and circumstance of life."], "category": "spiritual"}, {"name": "Maker", "notes": ["Captures Casey's love for building, creating, and bringing ideas into reality through hands-on work and inventive thinking."], "category": "passions_and_talents"}, {"name": "Problem Solver", "notes": ["Captures Casey's natural ability to tackle challenges and find creative solutions across different areas of life, from software engineering to hands-on projects."], "category": "passions_and_talents"}, {"name": "Pianist", "notes": ["Captures Casey's love for playing the piano and expressing creativity through music."], "category": "passions_and_talents"}, {"name": "Hard Worker", "notes": ["Captures Casey's steady, reliable energy and commitment to providing for his family through consistent effort and dedication in earning a living."], "category": "maker_of_money"}, {"name": "Steward", "notes": ["Captures Casey's channeling of his grandmother's wisdom and thoughtful, responsible approach to managing and protecting his finances."], "category": "keeper_of_money"}, {"name": "Clean Cut", "notes": ["Captures Casey's intentional, put-together approach to personal appearance, balancing a polished look with readiness for hands-on work."], "state": "accepted", "category": "personal_appearance"}, {"name": "Maintainer", "notes": ["Captures Casey's steady, practical approach to caring for his bodyâ€”valuing health and capability, even when time is limited for formal workouts."], "state": "accepted", "category": "physical_expression"}, {"name": "Pillar", "notes": ["Captures Casey's desire to be a solid foundation of strength, stability, and support for his immediate family, especially after experiencing significant family loss."], "state": "accepted", "category": "familial_relations"}, {"name": "Conductor", "notes": ["Captures Casey's ability to orchestrate and coordinate the practical tasks of life, drawing on his musical background and leadership energy to bring order and harmony to daily responsibilities."], "state": "accepted", "category": "doer_of_things"}], "user_notes": [{"note": "Grew up in Norcross, GA, a suburb of Atlanta, and moved to Homer, GA, a rural area, at age 15.", "created_at": "2025-08-02T17:15:17.831083+00:00"}, {"note": "Moved to the countryside to be closer to maternal grandparents, particularly close to grandmother who loved the country and farming.", "created_at": "2025-08-02T17:15:17.832698+00:00"}, {"note": "Initially resisted fitting in with new community, aligned with outsiders, later found a more supportive group of friends for several years.", "created_at": "2025-08-02T17:15:17.834029+00:00"}, {"note": "Self-taught software engineer with a background as a control room operator at a nuclear power plant.", "created_at": "2025-08-02T17:15:17.835285+00:00"}, {"note": "Moved to Malaga, Spain, about 4 years ago with wife, prompting a career change to full stack development.", "created_at": "2025-08-02T17:15:17.836592+00:00"}, {"note": "Enjoys the flexibility of working from home and setting own hours as a full stack developer", "created_at": "2025-08-02T17:15:17.837949+00:00"}, {"note": "Enjoys traveling with family, especially now that children are old enough to join.", "created_at": "2025-08-02T17:15:17.839287+00:00"}, {"note": "Has a deep interest in woodworking, previously had a full wood shop in the garage.", "created_at": "2025-08-02T17:15:17.840567+00:00"}, {"note": "Experienced significant family loss, with only two brothers remaining from immediate family. Has a strained relationship with one brother due to a dispute over inheritance.", "created_at": "2025-08-02T17:15:17.841967+00:00"}, {"note": "Lives in Spain with wife, two children, and mother-in-law.", "created_at": "2025-08-02T17:15:17.843179+00:00"}, {"note": "Experiencing a lack of motivation and feeling stuck in a rut, seeking to improve follow-through on personal goals.", "created_at": "2025-08-02T17:15:17.844324+00:00"}, {"note": "Father of two children", "created_at": "2025-08-02T17:15:17.845583+00:00"}, {"note": "Enjoys playing the piano", "created_at": "2025-08-02T17:15:17.846910+00:00"}, {"note": "Channels grandmother's wisdom for financial decisions, reflecting her influence in being wise with money.", "created_at": "2025-08-02T17:15:17.848238+00:00"}, {"note": "Has an aversion to any kind of religion and does not identify as spiritual", "created_at": "2025-08-02T17:15:17.849457+00:00"}], "coach_state": {"who_you_are": ["Dad", "Carpenter", "Engineer", "Hard Worker"], "current_phase": "identity_refinement", "identity_focus": "passions_and_talents", "who_you_want_to_be": ["Business Owner", "Good Public Speaker"], "skipped_identity_categories": ["romantic_relation"]}, "chat_messages": [{"role": "coach", "content": "Hi! It's nice to meet you! My name is Leigh Ann.", "timestamp": "2025-08-02T17:15:17.632418+00:00"}, {"role": "user", "content": "Hi!", "timestamp": "2025-08-02T17:15:17.634021+00:00"}, {"role": "coach", "content": "To get us started, I'd like to explain a little bit about what we're going to do together here so you've got an idea of how all this is going to work. Are you ok with that?", "timestamp": "2025-08-02T17:15:17.635432+00:00"}, {"role": "user", "content": "That sounds great", "timestamp": "2025-08-02T17:15:17.636865+00:00"}, {"role": "coach", "content": "Perfect! So here's the thing - most people try to change their lives through brute force and willpower. Like telling themselves 'I need to work out more' or 'I should save money.' But willpower always runs out, right?\\n\\nWhat we're going to do differently is start with Identity. So instead of forcing yourself to go to the gym, you become a Warrior who naturally trains. Instead of stressing about money, you become a Wealth Architect who builds abundance.\\n\\nCan you see the distinction between those two approaches?", "timestamp": "2025-08-02T17:15:17.638244+00:00"}, {"role": "user", "content": "I can", "timestamp": "2025-08-02T17:15:17.639585+00:00"}, {"role": "coach", "content": "Great! So instead of organizing your life into external buckets like Career, Health, Finance, we flip it inward. We ask 'Who are you in relationship to your health?' Maybe you're a Warrior, or an Athlete, or a Vitality Seeker.\\n\\nDoes that make sense to you?", "timestamp": "2025-08-02T17:15:17.640949+00:00"}, {"role": "user", "content": "It does", "timestamp": "2025-08-02T17:15:17.642219+00:00"}, {"role": "coach", "content": "Here's the cool part - you're not just one thing. You might be a Warrior with your health, a Wealth Architect with money, and a Loving Partner in relationships. We're going to create a bunch of different Identities that represent these different parts of you. Pretty wild concept, right?", "timestamp": "2025-08-02T17:15:17.643484+00:00"}, {"role": "user", "content": "Yeah", "timestamp": "2025-08-02T17:15:17.644721+00:00"}, {"role": "coach", "content": "And here's how it works day-to-day. Instead of forcing yourself through tasks, you just ask 'Who needs to handle this?' Then you step into that identity. So if you need to tackle your budget, you don't struggle with it - you let your Wealth Architect handle it. Makes sense when you think about it that way.\\n\\nWhat do you think about applying this approach to your daily life?", "timestamp": "2025-08-02T17:15:17.645995+00:00"}, {"role": "user", "content": "I think I'm going to like this", "timestamp": "2025-08-02T17:15:17.647241+00:00"}, {"role": "coach", "content": "Wonderful! I'm excited to dive deeper with you. Before we get into the actual Identity work, I'd love to get to know you better. The more I understand about you and your world, the better I can help. So let's chat - I'll ask you some questions, and you can share as much or as little as feels right. Sound good?", "timestamp": "2025-08-02T17:15:17.648408+00:00"}, {"role": "user", "content": "That sounds great", "timestamp": "2025-08-02T17:15:17.649614+00:00"}, {"role": "coach", "content": "Fantastic! Let's start with something simple. Where did you grow up?", "timestamp": "2025-08-02T17:15:17.650820+00:00"}, {"role": "user", "content": "My early childhood was in Norcross, GA, a suburb on the north side of Atlanta. When I was 15, we moved to Homer, GA which was about an hour north of my Norcross home in the country", "timestamp": "2025-08-02T17:15:17.652016+00:00"}, {"role": "coach", "content": "That sounds like quite a shift from suburbia to the countryside! How did that move impact you? Did you find it challenging or did you enjoy the change?", "timestamp": "2025-08-02T17:15:17.653245+00:00"}, {"role": "user", "content": "It was a love hate thing really. We moved up there to be closer to my grandparents on my moms side, who I was very close with. My Grandmother loved the country and animals and farming and all that. They owned 165 acres in Homer since before I was born and they moved there in the late 1990's. So I was happy to be with them but I didn't fit in very much with the country crowd. I felt like an outsider.", "timestamp": "2025-08-02T17:15:17.654515+00:00"}, {"role": "coach", "content": "It sounds like you had a deep connection with your grandparents, especially your grandmother, which must have been comforting during the move. Being close to family can be such a blessing, even if the environment feels a bit foreign. Itâ€™s understandable to feel like an outsider when transitioning to a new setting, especially one so different from what you were used to. How did you navigate those feelings of being an outsider? Did you find any ways to connect with the new community or did you find solace in other areas?", "timestamp": "2025-08-02T17:15:17.655849+00:00"}, {"role": "user", "content": "No I dug my heels in on being different. I didn't want to have anything to do with the regular crowd so I found the outsiders group. In hindsight, I would have been better off not hanging out with them. I eventually did find a better group of friends that I stayed with for a few years.", "timestamp": "2025-08-02T17:15:17.657077+00:00"}, {"role": "coach", "content": "It's interesting how sometimes our initial choices, even if they don't seem ideal in hindsight, can lead us to valuable lessons and eventually to the right people. It sounds like you found your way to a group that resonated more with who you were becoming. \\n\\nLet's shift gears a bitâ€”I'd love to hear about what you're doing these days. What do you do for a living, and how did you find your way into that field?", "timestamp": "2025-08-02T17:15:17.658276+00:00"}, {"role": "user", "content": "I guess you could say I'm a software engineer though I have no formal training. I used to be a control room operator at a nuclear power plant. My wife is from Spain and about 4 years ago we decided to move to Malaga. That required a career change so I taught myself how to be a full stack developer", "timestamp": "2025-08-02T17:15:17.659589+00:00"}, {"role": "coach", "content": "Wow, that's quite a journey! Transitioning from a control room operator at a nuclear power plant to a self-taught full stack developer is impressive. It takes a lot of dedication and adaptability to make such a significant career shift, especially when moving to a new country like Spain. How has this change impacted your life and your sense of identity? Do you find that your work as a developer aligns with who you are or who you want to become?", "timestamp": "2025-08-02T17:15:17.660891+00:00"}, {"role": "user", "content": "Yes - though I really do miss my old job. But this one is interesting enough and challenging enough to keep me occupied and sufficiently stimulated. There are a lot of benefits as well. I can work from home and I get to make my own hours.", "timestamp": "2025-08-02T17:15:17.662125+00:00"}, {"role": "coach", "content": "It sounds like you've found a balance that works well for you, even if there are aspects of your old job that you miss. The flexibility and autonomy of working from home can be incredibly rewarding, especially when it aligns with your lifestyle and personal goals. \\n\\nSince we've touched on your career and the transition you've made, I'd love to hear a bit about your life outside of work. What are some things you love to do in your free time? Any hobbies or interests that are a big part of your life?", "timestamp": "2025-08-02T17:15:17.663332+00:00"}, {"role": "user", "content": "I really like to travel. I did that a lot with my wife a while back - before we had kids. Now that they are old enough, we're starting to travel again and I'm really happy about that. I like a wide variety of other things. I played the piano for a long time (haven't played seriously in many years though), I really enjoy woodworking and I had a full blown wood shop in my garage when I lived in the states.", "timestamp": "2025-08-02T17:15:17.664558+00:00"}, {"role": "coach", "content": "It sounds like you have a rich tapestry of interests! Traveling with your family must be such a wonderful way to create new memories together. It's great that you're able to share those experiences with your kids now that they're old enough.\\n\\nYour passion for woodworking and music adds such a creative dimension to your life. Having had a full-blown wood shop must have been a fantastic outlet for your creativity and craftsmanship. Do you find that these hobbies influence how you approach your work or other areas of your life?\\n\\nBefore we move on, I'd love to hear a little about your family if you're comfortable sharing. Who's in your world these days?", "timestamp": "2025-08-02T17:15:17.665927+00:00"}, {"role": "user", "content": "Honestly, not many are left. My Father died 20 years ago from lung cancer. My Grandmother (the one who likes farming and animals) died 3 years after that. Both my fathers parents passed away. My mothers dad died as well. And then my mother died last year. All that is left from my immediate family is 2 brothers. One of them I don't talk to because we got in a huge fight over my mothers inheritance. \\nI have my wife and two children who live with me here in Spain. My wife only has her mother as immediate family - she lives with us too.", "timestamp": "2025-08-02T17:15:17.667200+00:00"}, {"role": "coach", "content": "Thank you for sharing that with me. It sounds like you've experienced a lot of loss, and I can imagine how challenging that must have been. It's wonderful that you have your wife, children, and mother-in-law with you in Spain, creating a new chapter together. Family dynamics can be complex, especially when it comes to things like inheritance, and it's understandable that these situations can create distance.\\n\\nWith your family and interests in mind, I'm curious about what you're hoping to get out of this coaching journey. Is there a particular area of your life you're looking to explore or transform?", "timestamp": "2025-08-02T17:15:17.668528+00:00"}, {"role": "user", "content": "I just feel like I'm in a rut. I'm finding it hard to follow through on any of what I want to do. I know what I should be doing but I just don't have the motivation to actually do anything when the rubber hits the road. Id like to try and fix that if I can.", "timestamp": "2025-08-02T17:15:17.669883+00:00"}, {"role": "coach", "content": "Thank you for being so open about where you're at. Feeling stuck can be really frustrating, especially when you know what you want to achieve but can't seem to muster the motivation to get there. This is a great starting point for our work together.\\n\\nWe're going to explore the different identities you inhabit in your life right nowâ€”these could be roles, qualities, or ways you see yourself, big or small. By understanding who you are today, we can start to uncover the natural motivations and energies that might be lying dormant.\\n\\nOnce we've explored who you are today, we'll also look at who you might want to become in the future. How does that sound?", "timestamp": "2025-08-02T17:15:17.724193+00:00"}, {"role": "user", "content": "Sounds good to me", "timestamp": "2025-08-02T17:15:17.726051+00:00"}, {"role": "coach", "content": "Great! Let's dive into it. To start, think about the different roles and identities you currently embody in your life. These could be related to your work, family, hobbies, or any other aspect of your life. For example, you might identify as a software engineer, a father, a husband, or even a woodworking enthusiast.\\n\\nTake a moment and share with me who you are right now.", "timestamp": "2025-08-02T17:15:17.727503+00:00"}, {"role": "user", "content": "Dad is a good one since I have 2 kids. \\nCarpenter is a good one. Engineer I like", "timestamp": "2025-08-02T17:15:17.728955+00:00"}, {"role": "coach", "content": "I love those! Being a dad is such a profound identity, especially with two kids keeping you on your toes. And it's wonderful to see your passion for carpentry and engineering shining throughâ€”those are such creative and analytical roles, respectively.\\n\\nWhat else comes to mind? Are there any other roles or qualities that you feel are part of who you are right now?", "timestamp": "2025-08-02T17:15:17.730370+00:00"}, {"role": "user", "content": "I work hard.", "timestamp": "2025-08-02T17:15:17.731774+00:00"}, {"role": "coach", "content": "That's a fantastic quality to acknowledgeâ€”being a hard worker is such a valuable part of who you are, especially when balancing roles as a dad, carpenter, and engineer. It speaks to your dedication and perseverance.\\n\\nLet's capture these identities: Dad, Carpenter, Engineer, and Hard Worker.\\n\\nNow, let's stretch this a little. Who do you aspire to be? Think about any dreams or roles you haven't stepped into yet but feel drawn to. It could be something related to your passions, like woodworking, or even a completely new venture. What comes to mind?", "timestamp": "2025-08-02T17:15:17.733195+00:00"}, {"role": "user", "content": "I want to be a business owner", "timestamp": "2025-08-02T17:15:17.734436+00:00"}, {"role": "coach", "content": "That's an exciting aspiration! Becoming a business owner can open up so many possibilities for creativity and independence. It aligns beautifully with your skills in engineering and carpentry, perhaps even allowing you to blend those talents into a unique venture.\\n\\nLet's add \\"Business Owner\\" to your aspirational identities. Is there anything else that comes to mind when you think about who you want to become? Maybe something related to your love for woodworking or another passion?", "timestamp": "2025-08-02T17:15:17.735738+00:00"}, {"role": "user", "content": "I want to be a good public speaker.", "timestamp": "2025-08-02T17:15:17.737024+00:00"}, {"role": "coach", "content": "That's a wonderful aspiration! Being a good public speaker can enhance your ability to share your ideas and passions, whether it's about your work, your experiences, or even your journey as a business owner. It can also be a powerful tool for personal growth and connecting with others.\\n\\nLet's add \\"Good Public Speaker\\" to your list of aspirational identities. Here's what we have so far:\\n\\n- **Who You Are**: Dad, Carpenter, Engineer, Hard Worker\\n- **Who You Want To Be**: Business Owner, Good Public Speaker\\n\\nIs there anything else you'd like to add, or do you feel ready to move on to the next step?", "timestamp": "2025-08-02T17:15:17.738268+00:00"}, {"role": "user", "content": "I think we could move on for now", "timestamp": "2025-08-02T17:15:17.739433+00:00"}, {"role": "coach", "content": "Great! Now, let's make sure we're covering all the critical areas of your life. Let us create a balanced, powerful, and intentional version of you so you are fully expressed across every area of your life. This next step is where you might find that you're avoiding stepping into an identity, especially due to past trauma or experiences - know that where you find resistance is where you have the biggest opportunity for growth.\\n\\nI'll walk you through a few key categories, and we'll try to create at least one identity in each area of your life. If you don't have an identity for a category yet, don't worryâ€”this is a chance to choose who you want to become. Our very first area of focus will be **Passions and Talents**. This is where we'll explore what truly lights you up and makes you feel aliveâ€”those unique things you're naturally drawn to, whether it's your creativity, intellectual curiosities, or anything else that makes you lose track of time. How does that sound to get us started?\\"", "timestamp": "2025-08-02T17:15:17.740714+00:00"}, {"role": "user", "content": "Sounds great", "timestamp": "2025-08-02T17:15:17.742090+00:00"}, {"role": "coach", "content": "Fantastic! Let's dive into your Passions and Talents. These are the aspects of you that make you uniquely youâ€”your natural skills, interests, and the qualities that define your personality. Given your background as a carpenter and software engineer, along with your love for woodworking, I can already see some potential identities emerging.\\n\\nLet's explore a few questions to help us identify these passions and talents:\\n\\n1. **What activities make you completely lose track of time?**\\n2. **When do you feel most energized and alive?**\\n3. **What do people consistently come to you for or compliment you on?**\\n\\nFeel free to share anything that comes to mind, and we'll start shaping these into identities that truly resonate with who you are.", "timestamp": "2025-08-02T17:15:17.743388+00:00"}, {"role": "user", "content": "I like to make things", "timestamp": "2025-08-02T17:15:17.744712+00:00"}, {"role": "coach", "content": "That makes so much sense, Casey! The way you light up about woodworking and building things really speaks to a core part of who you are. I'm hearing a strong \\"Maker\\" or \\"Creator\\" energy in youâ€”someone who brings ideas into reality with their hands and mind.\\n\\nDoes the identity name \\"Maker\\" resonate with you for this part of your passions and talents? Or would you prefer something like \\"Builder,\\" \\"Creator,\\" or another word that feels even more true to you? Let me know which one feels right, or suggest your own!", "timestamp": "2025-08-02T17:15:17.746013+00:00"}, {"role": "user", "content": "I think I like Maker actually", "timestamp": "2025-08-02T17:15:17.747257+00:00"}, {"role": "coach", "content": "Wonderful! \\"Maker\\" is such a strong, grounded identity for youâ€”it really captures that hands-on, creative energy you bring to everything from woodworking to software engineering. I love how it honors both your craftsmanship and your inventive spirit.\\n\\nNow, letâ€™s keep exploring. Passions and Talents often have more than one facet. Besides being a Maker, are there other parts of you that feel distinctâ€”maybe when youâ€™re problem-solving, helping others, or diving into something youâ€™re deeply curious about? What else makes you feel most like yourself?", "timestamp": "2025-08-02T17:15:17.748573+00:00"}, {"role": "user", "content": "Problem Solver sounds good too", "timestamp": "2025-08-02T17:15:17.749858+00:00"}, {"role": "coach", "content": "\\"Problem Solver\\" is a fantastic addition, Casey! That really highlights your knack for tackling challenges and finding creative solutionsâ€”whether it's in your software work, woodworking projects, or even navigating life's curveballs. \\n\\nWould you like to lock in \\"Problem Solver\\" as another core identity for your passions and talents? Or is there a different word or phrase that feels even more spot-on for this part of you? Let me know if \\"Problem Solver\\" fits, or if you'd like to tweak it!", "timestamp": "2025-08-02T17:15:17.751181+00:00"}, {"role": "user", "content": "Yeah lets lock it in.", "timestamp": "2025-08-02T17:15:17.752390+00:00"}, {"role": "coach", "content": "Great! \\"Problem Solver\\" is officially part of your core set of passions and talents. You now have \\"Maker\\" and \\"Problem Solver\\"â€”two powerful facets that really capture your unique energy.\\n\\nLetâ€™s check in: Are there any other aspects of your personality or talents that feel distinct from these two? Maybe something like \\"Teacher,\\" \\"Innovator,\\" \\"Connector,\\" or even something totally different? Or do you feel complete with your Passions & Talents identities for now?", "timestamp": "2025-08-02T17:15:17.753664+00:00"}, {"role": "user", "content": "I really like to play the piano", "timestamp": "2025-08-02T17:15:17.754909+00:00"}, {"role": "coach", "content": "I love that, Casey! Playing the piano is such a beautiful expression of creativity and emotion. When you sit down at the keys, do you feel like a â€œMusician,â€ or does another word capture that part of you betterâ€”maybe â€œPerformer,â€ â€œComposer,â€ or even something more playful like â€œImproviserâ€? What identity name feels most true for the part of you that comes alive at the piano?", "timestamp": "2025-08-02T17:15:17.756196+00:00"}, {"role": "user", "content": "Lets go with Pianist for now on that one", "timestamp": "2025-08-02T17:15:17.757495+00:00"}, {"role": "coach", "content": "\\"Pianist\\" is a wonderful addition to your core set of passions and talents, Casey. I can just imagine the energy and focus you bring to the pianoâ€”thereâ€™s something so special about that creative outlet.\\n\\nSo now you have \\"Maker,\\" \\"Problem Solver,\\" and \\"Pianist.\\" Thatâ€™s a rich, multidimensional foundation! Would you like to explore if there are any other aspects of your passions or talents that feel distinct from these three? For example, is there a side of you that loves teaching, mentoring, storytelling, or maybe something else that lights you up? Or do you feel complete with your Passions & Talents identities for now?", "timestamp": "2025-08-02T17:15:17.758821+00:00"}, {"role": "user", "content": "I think I feel complete with these now", "timestamp": "2025-08-02T17:15:17.760847+00:00"}, {"role": "coach", "content": "Beautiful, Casey! Youâ€™ve got a strong foundation with \\"Maker,\\" \\"Problem Solver,\\" and \\"Pianist\\"â€”each one captures a unique and vibrant part of you. Letâ€™s carry that energy forward into the next area: who you are when it comes to making money.\\n\\nGiven your journey from nuclear power plant operator to self-taught software engineer, and now enjoying the flexibility of working from home in Spain, Iâ€™m curiousâ€”who is the part of you that shows up to earn a living? Is there a distinct identity that comes to mind, like \\"Innovator,\\" \\"Provider,\\" \\"Entrepreneur,\\" or maybe something else entirely? What name feels true for the part of you that creates income for your family?", "timestamp": "2025-08-02T17:15:17.762074+00:00"}, {"role": "user", "content": "I think this would definitely be my Hard worker.", "timestamp": "2025-08-02T17:15:17.763311+00:00"}, {"role": "coach", "content": "\\"Hard Worker\\" is such a grounded and honest identity for the part of you that shows up to provide for your family, Casey. It really honors the steady, reliable energy you bringâ€”whether youâ€™re learning a new skill, taking on a project, or just doing what needs to be done. \\n\\nWould you like to go with \\"Hard Worker\\" as your Maker of Money identity, or is there another word or phrase that feels even more energizing or true for you in this area? Sometimes people like to elevate it a bitâ€”like \\"Dedicated Provider,\\" \\"Resourceful Earner,\\" or \\"Steadfast Builder\\"â€”but \\"Hard Worker\\" is absolutely valid if thatâ€™s what resonates most. What feels right to you?", "timestamp": "2025-08-02T17:15:17.764443+00:00"}, {"role": "user", "content": "Lets just go with Hard worker for now", "timestamp": "2025-08-02T17:15:17.765724+00:00"}, {"role": "coach", "content": "Great, Casey! \\"Hard Worker\\" is now your Maker of Money identity. This honors the steady, reliable energy you bring to supporting your family and creating opportunitiesâ€”no matter what field youâ€™re in or where life takes you.\\n\\nNow, letâ€™s shift gears. The next area is all about keeping and growing the money you make. This is a totally different energy from making moneyâ€”itâ€™s less about hustle and more about stewardship, strategy, and sometimes even restraint. \\n\\nWho is the part of you that manages, saves, invests, or protects your resources? Is there a name or vibe that comes to mind for the identity that takes care of your money once itâ€™s earned?", "timestamp": "2025-08-02T17:15:17.766959+00:00"}, {"role": "user", "content": "I channel my grandmother for this. She was always wise with her money and taught me to be the same way. Whenever I make a decision about my finances, I try think about what she would think about my decision.", "timestamp": "2025-08-02T17:15:17.768215+00:00"}, {"role": "coach", "content": "Casey, I absolutely love that you channel your grandmotherâ€™s wisdom when it comes to managing your finances. Thatâ€™s such a beautiful way to honor her legacy and keep her spirit alive in your daily life. \\n\\nWould you like to call this identity something like \\"The Steward,\\" \\"The Wise Keeper,\\" or even \\"The Grandmotherâ€™s Voice\\"? Or is there another name that captures the energy and guidance you feel from her when youâ€™re making financial decisions? Letâ€™s find a name that feels both personal and powerful for this part of you.", "timestamp": "2025-08-02T17:15:17.769372+00:00"}, {"role": "user", "content": "I like Steward. That seems fitting. My grandma would like that.", "timestamp": "2025-08-02T17:15:17.770763+00:00"}, {"role": "coach", "content": "\\"Steward\\" is a beautiful choice, Casey. It really honors the wisdom and care your grandmother modeled for you, and it captures that sense of thoughtful responsibility you bring to managing your resources. I can just imagine her nodding in approval every time you make a decision with that energy.\\n\\nNow, letâ€™s move to the next area: your spiritual identity. This isnâ€™t about religion unless you want it to beâ€”itâ€™s about your connection to something bigger than yourself, whatever that means for you. Who are you when it comes to meaning, purpose, or your sense of the sacred? Is there a name or feeling that comes to mind for this part of you?", "timestamp": "2025-08-02T17:15:17.771925+00:00"}, {"role": "user", "content": "I'm not spiritual at all really. I actually have an aversion to any kind of religion", "timestamp": "2025-08-02T17:15:17.773364+00:00"}, {"role": "coach", "content": "Thank you for being so honest, Casey. I want you to know that thereâ€™s absolutely no pressure hereâ€”this isnâ€™t about religion or adopting any beliefs that donâ€™t feel true to you. For some people, their sense of meaning or connection comes from nature, family, creativity, or even just a deep appreciation for the mystery of life itself.\\n\\nIf you had to name the part of you that finds meaning or peaceâ€”even if itâ€™s just in the quiet moments, or in the beauty of a well-made object, or in the love you have for your familyâ€”what would you call that? Or, if youâ€™d rather skip this one for now, thatâ€™s perfectly okay too. What feels right to you?", "timestamp": "2025-08-02T17:15:17.774609+00:00"}, {"role": "user", "content": "I do think theres something to be said for keeping some perspective on how little we are and how lucky we are", "timestamp": "2025-08-02T17:15:17.775926+00:00"}, {"role": "coach", "content": "That perspective is so grounding, Casey. Thereâ€™s a real humility and gratitude in recognizing how small we are in the grand scheme of things, and how much of life is just sheer luck or circumstance. For some people, that sense of awe 